episodes.title: The Projected Man
episodes.plot: A scientist's experiment gone wrong gives him the touch of death while the SOL crew find themselves back in their old time period.

episodes.title: The Phantom Planet
episodes.plot: Killer peanut brittle terrorizes the universe while Pearl settles into her ancestral home by building a doomsday device.

episodes.title: The Pumaman
episodes.plot: Constantly-Out-Of-His-League Man battles evil while Pearl hosts her Castle Forrester Ball.

episodes.title: Werewolf
episodes.plot: A guy turns people into werewolves for his own sick pleasure while Mike turns into a were-Crow.

episodes.title: The Deadly Bees
episodes.plot: Killer bees terrify a remote English island while a bowler hatted guy appears where he's least expected.

episodes.title: The Space Children
episodes.plot: A blob from Heaven brainwashes children into doing his bidding while Pearl starts her own space program.

episodes.title: Hobgoblins
episodes.plot: Mike and the Bots suffer through the 1988 B movie "Hobgoblins," the story of tiny goblin-like creatures who attack a group of teenagers.

episodes.title: The Touch of Satan
episodes.plot: An overly obvious '70s wanderer hits on a witch while a babysitter watches over Castle Forrester.

episodes.title: Gorgo
episodes.plot: Mike and the 'bots gorge on Gorgo (1961), a maudlin monster mess featuring two giant mother-and-son lizards and a Samuel Beckett lookalike. Leonard Maltin shows up to hawk his movie guide, which inexplicably praises the film.

episodes.title: The Final Sacrifice
episodes.plot: It's "Canada Bashing Day" on the SOL in every respect between progressive world domination and bizarre looting.

episodes.title: Devil Fish
episodes.plot: A sea monster eats out for some Italian while dolphins seek revenge against the SOL.

episodes.title: The Screaming Skull
episodes.plot: A vengeful skull comes back from the dead and the bots are scarred for life when Gumby abuses his robot slaves.

episodes.title: Quest of the Delta Knights
episodes.plot: Pearl sits in on part of this week's experiment as part of her annual review, and Leonardo da Vinci stops by to insist the guy playing him in the film is a mook.
